<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV RATINGS; 'GRACE' TAKES OVER 'HOME' FOR SECOND WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For the second week in a row, "Grace Under Fire"edged out "Home Improvement" 
as the nation's top-rated TV program--although the local preference was for 
something altogether different: "Beverly Hills, 90210." 
</P>
<P>
 Besides the two Tuesday night comedies at the top of the national pack, ABC 
also won positions three and four with "NYPD Blue" and "Roseanne," propelling 
the network to a solid victory over its rivals and maintaining its front-runner 
status for the season. 
</P>
<P>
 The figures released Tuesday by the A.C. Nielsen Co. showed that the 
highest-rated movielast week was "Someone Else's Child" on ABC Sunday night, 
starring Lisa Hartman Black. It finished 14th among the week's 94 prime-time 
network programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite ranking first locally, "Beverly Hills, 90210" finished 37th 
nationally. And Fox's two Sunday night installments of "The Simpsons" ranked in 
the Top 10 locally but ranked 58th and 64th nationally. Nevertheless, Fox 
managed to inch by CBS in competition for the prized demographic group of 
viewers age 18 to 49, with ABC first and NBC second. Southland Ratings 
</P>
<P>
 Here are A.C. Nielsen's Top 10 prime-time programs in the Los Angeles area 
during the same week. Each rating point equals 50,064 households. 
04,05,27,08,06 Program Station Rating 1. Beverly Hills, 90210 KTTV 19.2 2. 
Seinfeld KNBC 19.0 3. 60 Minutes KCBS 18.0 4. Home Improvement KABC 18.0 5. The 
Simpsons (8:30 p.m.) KTTV 17.3 6. Married ... With Children KTTV 17.1 7. 
Roseanne KABC 16.8 8. Grace Under Fire KABC 16.4 9. The Simpsons KTTV 16.3 10. 
20/20 KABC 15.7 Weekly Averages 
</P>
<P>
 ABC: 12.6 CBS: 11.1 NBC: 10.7 FOX: 7.9 Season to Date 
</P>
<P>
 ABC: 12.2 CBS: 12.0 NBC: 11.5 FOX: 7.8LEE MARGULIES 
