<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISH REPORT: POND FOR POND, TEMECULA HAS A LAKE THAT'S LOADED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Corona Lake is more of a pond than a lake. One can row from one end to another 
without working up a sweat. 
</P>
<P>
 Therein lies the advantage because the small reservoir near Temecula is loaded 
with fish. 
</P>
<P>
 Or so it would seem, given the success recently of Jim Payne. The angler from 
Orange, casting mini-jigs near the dam and along the east shore, caught and 
released 30 crappie and 10 largemouth bass and then pulled from the lake his 
five-fish limit of trout. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
