<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; SANTA ANA VALLEY RALLIES TO WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fueled by a third-quarter rally, Santa Ana Valley defeated Chino Hills Ayala, 
65-60, in the first round of the In-N-Out Burger/Converse Classic on Tuesday at 
Trabuco Hills High. 
</P>
<P>
 After trailing, 30-22, at the half, the Falcons outscored Ayala, 17-8, in the 
third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Olujimi Mann had 21 points and Ike Harmon 20 for Santa Ana Valley (2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Tom Berry had 22 points and Shane Riggins added 18 for Ayala. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In other tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 94, South Torrance 69 -- David Lalazarian scored 29 points and Doug 
Gottlieb had 27 to lead Tustin, which led, 53-25, at halftime in the 
first-round game. 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 74, Rancho Bernardo 67 -- Randy Shepard scored 15 points to 
lead Capistrano Valley (2-1), which led, 38-24, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 65, Long Beach St. Anthony 57 -- Corey Holbert scored 21 points and 
Dan Ploog had 18 to lead La Habra (2-1), which outscored St. Anthony, 39-32, in 
the second half of the consolation game. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 71, Agoura 61 -- Paul Tayyar had 19 points and Daniel Keller 
15 to lead Fountain Valley in the consolation game. The Barons led, 33-24, at 
the half. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Costa Mesa tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel 64, Santiago 49 -- Isaac Leasau scored a game-high 19 points 
for Calvary Chapel (5-0). Teammate Joe Ortiz added 17 points and Brandon Wills 
13. Kevin Falconer had eight points and nine assists.  
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia 69, Los Amigos 52 -- Josh Reding was eight for nine from field 
scoring 19 points, to lead Magnolia (3-2). Teammate Ahmad Shurdim had 13 points 
and nine rebounds. Mark Udell scored a game-high 20 points for Los Amigos. 
</P>
<P>
 In the La Quinta Aztec Classic: 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 72, Westminster 51 -- Greg Greenfield had 16 points and Jason 
Gondringer added 16 for La Quinta (2-0). Mark Steele had 12 points for 
Westminster (2-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 44, Liberty Christian 32 -- Matt Jones scored 16 points and 
Jeremy Johnson 12 to lead Huntington Beach (1-0), which rallied from a 23-20 
halftime deficit. Bob McClung scored 18 points for Liberty Christian (3-2) in 
the first round. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague play: 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 87, Orange Lutheran 67 -- Marc Brown had 20 points and Dan Almquist 
added 19 for host Foothill (4-1). Matt Begatourian had 10 points to lead Orange 
Lutheran (2-2). 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's 62, San Clemente 52 -- Bobby Baker scored 18 points, including 
four three-pointers, to lead St. Margaret's (3-0). Damion Raibon added 11 
points and 11 rebounds and Bobby Masters had six points and 16 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo 59, Aliso Niguel 41 -- Tyler Kalklosch scored 19 points and Don 
Williams and Austin Moherman each added 10 points to lead host Mission Viejo 
(4-1). Jason Mulkay scored 13 points, including three three-pointers, for Aliso 
Niguel (1-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 65, Irvine 59 -- Donald Meyers had 19 points and Jeff Barnett added 
13 for host Dana Hills (1-1). Carl Madrioli led the Vaqueros with eight 
rebounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
