<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAIDERS; NO BREAK FOUND IN HOSTETLER'S HAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Many quarterbacks don't know if they have had good games until they have seen 
the films. Jeff Hostetler doesn't know if he's had a good game until he's seen 
the X-rays. 
</P>
<P>
 For the third time in four weeks, Hostetler has needed postgame medical tests. 
And for the third time, he has passed them. 
</P>
<P>
 X-rays of his injured left hand -- his non-throwing hand -- after Monday 
night's game against the San Diego Chargers were negative. Hostetler's left 
hand was cut when defensive back Darrien Gordon stepped on him as Hostetler 
rolled out of bounds. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a good thing it wasn't a defensive lineman," Hostetler said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gordon weighs 182 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Hostetler sat out three plays, then returned. 
</P>
<P>
 His left hand is bandaged, but he is not expected to miss any playing time. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders are reporting brisk sales for Sunday's game against the Denver 
Broncos, but tickets in all price categories remain and at this point, a 
sellout does not appear imminent. STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120794-0053 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 105598 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
