<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS; FARR EXPECTED TO GO ON INJURED LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Defensive tackle D'Marco Farr, who suffered a hyper-extended elbow Sunday 
against the New Orleans Saints, is expected to be put on injured reserve today 
and replaced on the roster by defensive end Jay Williams, who has been on the 
Rams' practice squad. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams thought the hiring of Wayne Sevier, acknowledged around the league as 
one of the game's premier special teams coaches, was going to make the 
difference in two or three games this season. 
</P>
<P>
 What has happened is not what they had in mind. Special teams blunders have 
figured prominently in several losses. 
</P>
<P>
 "There's no question about it," Sevier said. "I fully accept the fact I 
haven't gotten it done on special teams. Our special teams haven't done it, and 
I haven't been able to communicate and motivate in a way that I normally feel I 
can do. And that's my responsibility." 
</P>
<P>
 Ram special teams have given up four returns for touchdowns, and in the last 
two games, punt returner Todd Kinchen has fumbled the ball away three times. 
T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120794-0055 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 105600 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 7, 1994, Wednesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 6; Column 3 
</P>
