<P>
ICE UNDERNEATH, SLIPPERY ON TOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tuesday night's NBA game between the Phoenix Suns and Washington Bullets was 
postponed after a 90-minute delay because of moisture on the court at the USAir 
Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 The wetness was caused when humidity outside combined with the new ice surface 
under the court. The ice was for a figure-skating show. 
