<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Armand Boglin: Fullerton, Sophomore Football/Defensive back 
</P>
<P>
 Boglin, from Pomona High, had a solid regular season for the Hornets but 
didn't get the one thing defensive backs dream of -- an interception. But he 
changed that Saturday when he intercepted two passes as Fullerton beat Hancock, 
38-33, in the K-Swiss Bowl.He returned one interception 18 yards for touchdown 
that put Fullerton ahead, 31-21, in the third quarter. Boglin, who was the 
K-Swiss Bowl defensive player of the game, finished the season with 26 solo 
tackles and also was in on two sacks. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Football 
</P>
<P>
 James Hartford: Fullerton, sophomore.  
</P>
<P>
 Hartford rushed for 93 yards and caught eight passes for 39 yards as Fullerton 
beat Hancock, 38-33, in the K-Swiss Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Becca Foltz: Golden West, Sophomore Volleyball/Outside hitter 
</P>
<P>
 Foltz ended her sophomore season the same way she ended her freshman season -- 
with her best performance of the year. Foltz, from Foothill High, had 75 kills 
in four matches as Golden West won its second consecutive State title Sunday 
with a three-game sweep of Cerritos. Foltz had 17 kills in the championship 
match. Foltz, who was slowed by a pulled stomach muscle earlier this season, 
was selected as most valuable of the tournament for the second consecutive 
time. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Sara Works: Cypress, sophomore.  
</P>
<P>
 Works set a Cypress single-game record with 42 points as the Chargers beat 
Long Beach, 87-64, in a semifinal game of the Cypress tournament. 
</P>
