<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS SOCCER 1994-1995: SOCCER PREVIEW; SIX TEAMS TO WATCH; SANTA MARGARITA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: Curt Bauer (third year). 
</P>
<P>
 1993-94: 16-5-3, 7-4-1 in Sea View League; lost in semifinals of the Division 
IV playoffs to Riverside Poly, 2-2, on penalty kicks. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Mike Allred, sweeper, Sr.; Matt Blasdel, midfielder, Jr.; Matt 
Eberle, midfielder, Sr.; Seth George, forward, Sr.; Miguel Godoy, forward, Sr.; 
Chon Kantikovit, midfielder, Jr; Ryan Korinke, defender, Sr.; Tim Padayachee, 
defender, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: Paul Greco, defender, Sr.; Matt Moses, midfielder, So.; Brian 
Piesner, forward, Jr.; Bryce Popko, defender, Jr.; Shawn Saunders, defender, 
Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: The Eagles already were going to be formidable, based on their summer 
season -- two league titles and a runner-up. But with the addition of Piesner, 
who was the MVP of his high school team in Texas, they might be the best in the 
county. "He's got great skills," Bauer said of the left-footed Piesner. "He can 
pass, shoot -- a great package." Padayachee returns after missing last season 
with a broken foot, but Saunders will miss much of this season with the same 
injury. George was a Times' All-County first-team selection last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
