<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Courtney Blunt 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Birmingham 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Football 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Blunt has gained 1,528 yards in 248 carries (a 6.2-yard 
average) and has scored 22 touchdowns, third best among area City Section 
players. In the Braves' three playoff games, Blunt has rushed for 477 yards and 
six touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Blunt was one of the reasons the Braves won their City 3-A 
Division semifinal, rushing for 221 yards and scoring three touchdowns in 25 
carries. Blunt, a 6-foot, 170-pound tailback, had to accomplish most of his 
work without his fullback, Marvin Powell, who left the game in the first half 
because of a neck injury. "He's an exceptional back," Coach Chick Epstein said. 
"He's playing sensationally." 
</P>
