<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Elaine Canchola 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Nordhoff 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Freshman 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Canchola began her first cross-country season as an 
unknown but has developed into one of the nation's top performers in the last 
five weeks. She finished a surprising third in the Ventura County championships 
Oct. 28, won the Southern Section Division III title Nov. 19, and placed second 
in the State Division III final Nov. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Canchola placed second in the Foot Locker West regional at 
Fresno's Woodward Park on Saturday to advance to the national championships at 
San Diego's Balboa Park on Dec. 10. She and Agoura's Deena Drossin (1987) are 
the only freshmen to place that high since the meet began in 1979. 
</P>
