games and wound up winning the Orange County summer league. Fountain Valley 
starts three sophomores and two freshmen, Tolman and Sutagaki. But Smith said 
his young players are plenty talented. "We're very tough defensively and 
offensively, we go hard to the ball," Smith said. "We finish when we get our 
chances." Vazquez, who Smith thinks can be one of the county's best forwards, 
is Fountain Valley's best finisher. Ritter was an All-Sunset League first-team 
selection last season. 
