<P>
VOLLEYBALL COACH RESIGNS AT MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jason Bilbruck has resigned as coach of the Marina boys' and girls' volleyball 
teams, he said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Bilbruck, 22, coached the boys' and girls' teams the last two seasons, leading 
each to the Southern Section playoffs once. The boys finished fourth in the 
Sunset League last season and the girls were third last season (12-9, 7-5 in 
league). MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
