<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOWERS TO SPONSOR LAS POSADAS FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Bowers Museum of Cultural Art will hold the annual Las Posadas traditional 
Mexican Christmas festival at the museum on Dec. 18. 
</P>
<P>
 The museum's three-hour free event will feature folkloric dancers, live music 
and pinatas as well as traditional Las Posadas foods, including sweet tamales 
and sugar candies. 
</P>
<P>
 In Mexico, Las Posadas began in 1587, when an Augustan friar, Diego de Soria, 
was given permission by Pope Sixtus V to celebrate special masses outdoors in 
the days before Christmas. It evolved into the public processions that are 
commonplace today. 
</P>
<P>
 Bowers' Las Posadas celebration will run from 5:30 to 8:30 p.m. at the museum, 
2002 N. Main St., Santa Ana. Information: (714) 567-3600. 
</P>
</TEXT>
