CHRISTMAS ARRIVES EARLY FOR 3 DESTITUTE CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Claus, aided by an outpouring of community support, made Tuesday a 
Christmas to remember for three excited youngsters who police had found dirty 
and hungry when they responded to a domestic dispute. 
</P>
<P>
 The officers on Sunday found the destitute family of five living in a squalid 
house without electricity as the three children, ages 4, 3 and 23 months, 
shared a single taco, the only food in the house, said police spokesman Mike 
Halphen. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm looking at a room full of more than a hundred toys and clothes and candy, 
and it all started when the 4-year-old asked (an officer) if Santa would find 
them this year because last year he didn't," Halphen said. " . . . I wish 
everyone could have seen those little faces." 
