<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROBERTI NAMED TO STATE JOBLESS INSURANCE PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Recently retired state Sen. David A. Roberti (D-Van Nuys) has been appointed 
by the Senate Rules Committee to a four-year term on the state Unemployment 
Insurance Appeals Board at an annual salary of $97,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee met in private Monday to make the appointment of the veteran 
lawmaker. 
</P>
<P>
 Chairman Bill Lockyer (D-Hayward), who succeeded Roberti as Senate leader this 
year, said the vote was 4 to 0. Newly appointed committee member Sen. John 
Lewis (R-Orange) said he abstained because he did not have time to discuss the 
Roberti appointment with fellow Republicans. 
</P>
<P>
 It became known last week that Roberti was in line for appointment to the 
insurance panel, which hears appeals from workers who maintain that they were 
wrongfully denied unemployment benefits. 
