</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are investigating the weekend shooting of a man who apparently was 
critically wounded by two men who knew him. 
</P>
<P>
 Peter Montano, 35, was shot twice in front of his home in the 1800 block of 
Moorpark Drive at 8:40 p.m. Saturday, said Sgt. Ed McDonald. 
</P>
<P>
 Montano, who manages an auto parts store in Los Angeles, has not regained 
consciousness since being airlifted to an undisclosed hospital, McDonald said. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors told police that after he was shot with a handgun, Montano told them 
his two male attackers knew him. The attackers fled in a maroon car. 
</P>
<P>
 "He knew the people that were involved" but the nature of their relationship 
will not be known until he can be interviewed at the hospital, McDonald said. 
</P>
<P>
 He said that Montano's residence had been burglarized several weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't know if it's related or not to the shooting," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents were shaken by the attack, McDonald said. 
</P>
<P>
 "They're all scared and concerned about a shooting in the neighborhood," he 
said. "It's not something that happens there." MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
