BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TCI in Argentine, Japanese Cable Ventures: Tele-Communications Inc., the 
largest U.S. operator of cable TV systems, said it plans to acquire 80% of 
Buenos Aires-based Cablevision de Argentina.Terms of the deal, which is subject 
to the approval of Argentine regulators, were not disclosed. Cablevision, with 
450,000 customers, is one of the largest cable operators in Argentina. TCI also 
announced the formation of Jupiter Telecommunications, a joint venture with 
Sumitomo Corp. of Japan. Jupiter will manage cable systems and aims to offer 
telephone service eventually. In Japan, six Sumitomo cable systems serving 
775,000 households in the Tokyo area will be transferred to Jupiter. Sumitomo 
will have a 60% interest; TCI will have the other 40%. 
</P>
