</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Northrop Grumman Gets Navy Computer Contract: The $155-million engineering and 
manufacturing development project is to upgrade the mission computer in E-2C 
Hawkeye airborne early-warning and control aircraft. The contract is one of the 
first under a Defense Department initiative toward increased use of commercial, 
off-the-shelf equipment in military systems. Northrop Grumman will install the 
new mission computer in future E-2Cs and will produce kits to retrofit current 
Hawkeyes. The engineering development and software integration will be done on 
Long Island, N.Y. 
</P>
