<P>
 New York Times Co. Expands Into Electronic Media: The publisher said it plans 
to spend at least $1 billion buying local television stations and cable 
networks and developing programming.Executives described the outlays, to be 
spread over five or six years, as a diversification effort aimed at reducing 
the company's reliance on newspapers for about 90% of its profit. The company, 
which owns the New York Times and 28 regional newspapers, also announced the 
launch of a new on-line service by its Boston Globe newspaper. It already 
operates an electronic outlet through America On-Line, called @Times. 
