<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFICARE TAPS TEXAS EXECUTIVE TO HEAD CALIFORNIA UNIT; HMO: JON WAMPLER WILL 
ASSUME HIS DUTIES AS PRESIDENT AND CEO BY FEB. 1, THE CHIEF OF THE 
CYPRESS-BASED PARENT COMPANY SAYS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON LEE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PacifiCare Health Systems Inc. has chosen Jon Wampler, its top executive in 
Texas, to be president and chief executive officer of the health maintenance 
organization's operations in California. 
</P>
<P>
 The appointment, to be announced publicly today, follows the unexpected 
departure of Jeffrey Folick, who resigned in October as president and CEO of 
PacifiCare of California to take a job with a large Minneapolis-based HMO. 
</P>
<P>
 Wampler, 43, has been president of PacifiCare of Texas since August, 1990, 
when he joined the company. He will assume his new duties by Feb. 1, said Alan 
Hoops, president and CEO of PacifiCare Health Systems, the national parent 
company. 
</P>
<P>
 Wampler will now also be a vice president of PacifiCare Health Systems, which 
has 1.2 million members overall. Half of them are with PacifiCare of 
California, the company's principal subsidiary, with the rest in Florida, 
Oklahoma, Oregon, Texas and Washington. 
</P>
<P>
 Hoops said in an interview Tuesday that Wampler was one of three final 
candidates. "The thing we liked about Jon is that he's a team-oriented 
executive. He's built an atmosphere of cooperation and teamwork," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 He noted that Wampler, like his predecessor in California, had built up the 
HMO's business for Medicare recipients, which has become an important part of 
PacifiCare's growth. "We're really looking for him to provide the glue to 
maintain the growth of PacifiCare of California," Hoops said. 
</P>
<P>
 Wampler, who could not be reached for comment, has 16 years of experience in 
the industry. Before joining PacifiCare, he was executive director of Humana 
Health Care Plans of Colorado. He had also worked at MetLife HealthCare 
Network, also in Colorado.  
</P>
<P>
 Wampler lives in San Antonio with his wife and daughter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
